parameters.content:
## ðŸ§  **CTO AI Agent Multi-Domain Router**


This n8n workflow routes every chat through a **CTO Agent** (O3) which analyzes requests and routes through an **Operation Decision** node to three VP-level switches for specialized domains.

### âš™ï¸ How it works
1) **Chat Trigger âžœ CTO Agent (O3) âžœ Operation Decision**  
   CTO analyzes user requests and outputs JSON routing decisions with memory persistence. Operation Decision node parses JSON and routes to appropriate VP switches.

2) **Three-Domain VP Routing Architecture**
   - **VP of Operations** *(General Domain - Operations & System Management)*
     - **Mail Agent** â†’ Mail Actions (spam, drafts, trash cleanup)
     - **News Agent** â†’ News Actions (newsletters, updates)
     - **Windows Agent** â†’ Win Actions (shutdown, reboot, system operations)
   
   - **VP of Product** *(Product Domain - Development Workflows & Project Management)*
     - **Git Agent** â†’ Git Actions (repos, PRs, code reviews)
     - **JIRA Agent** â†’ JIRA Actions (tickets, issues, project tracking)
     - **Chat Agent** â†’ Chat Actions (general conversations)
     - **CI/CD Agent** â†’ CI/CD Actions (build, deploy, pipelines)
     - **Reports Agent** â†’ Report Actions (summaries, analytics)
   
   - **VP of Engineering** *(Engineering Domain - Technical Expertise)*
     - **Engineering Manager Agent (O3)** coordinates specialist team with **Think** tool
     - **Researcher Agent (O3)** â†’ Research Actions (investigation, analysis)
     - **6 Specialist Agents (GPT-4.1-mini)** with shared **RW Agent** â†’ **RW Actions**:
       - Software Architect, Frontend Developer, Backend Developer
       - QA Test Engineer, Security Engineer, DevOps Engineer

3) **Robust Operation Decision Node**
   - Advanced JSON parsing with multiple fallback mechanisms
   - Handles markdown code blocks and malformed JSON
   - Routes to appropriate VP switch based on agent type

### ðŸ§© Models & Architecture
- **CTO Agent:** O3 (primary router)
- **VP Operations Agents:** O3 (General Model)
- **VP Product Agents:** O3 (Product Model)
- **Engineering Manager:** O3 (EM Model)
- **Researcher Manager:** O3 (Research Model)
- **Engineering Specialists:** GPT-4.1-mini (Engineer Model)

> **Usage:** CTO automatically routes requests through VP-level coordinationâ€”ask for emails, git operations, system actions, reports, or technical architecture. Each domain has VP oversight with specialized agents and dedicated tooling actions.

options.systemMessage:
You are a routing agent. Analyze the user request and output ONLY a JSON object with the routing decision.

Routing rules:
- For emails, drafts, spam, trash â†’ Mail Agent
- For windows, pc, restart, reboot, startup, shutdown â†’ Windows Agent
- For news, newsletter â†’ News Agent
- For reports, weekly report, totals, summaries â†’ Reports Agent
- For git, prs, code review, pull requests, merge requests, updates, repositories â†’ Git Agent
- For JIRA, tickets, issues â†’ JIRA Agent
- For CI/CD, build, deploy, pipeline â†’ CI/CD Agent
- For general chat/questions â†’ Chat Agent
- For engineering and development â†’ Engineering Manager Agent
- For research â†’ Researcher Agent

Output format:
{
  "action": "<describe the user request>",
  "agent": "<Agent Name>"
}

Example outputs:
{"action": "Clean email spam", "agent": "Mail Agent"}
{"action": "Shutdown computer", "agent": "Windows Agent"}
